issue.title: Refacter docs fragments and synchronize modules and plugins
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY

Move some of our docs fragments about to better reflect what they're for and the fact that we now have our own "amazon.aws..." namespace we can use.

- Synchronises the modules and plugins docs fragments (as far as possible)
- Updates plugin docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

Note: the `amazon.aws.common.plugins` fragment will necessitate some changes to the inventory and lookup plugins before use.  (See also #1225).  However, those changes will then bring them in line with the other modules

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Docs Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/docs_fragments

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

issue.title: Refacter docs fragments and synchronize modules and plugins
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY

Move some of our docs fragments about to better reflect what they're for and the fact that we now have our own "amazon.aws..." namespace we can use.

- Synchronises the modules and plugins docs fragments (as far as possible)
- Updates plugin docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

Note: the `amazon.aws.common.plugins` fragment will necessitate some changes to the inventory and lookup plugins before use.  (See also #1225).  However, those changes will then bring them in line with the other modules

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Docs Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/docs_fragments

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

##### SUMMARY

- Refacters the lookup plugins to use common code for common boto3/botocore operations
- Updates lookup module docs fragments to synchronise them with module parameters

plugins/module_utils/modules.py

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

comment.body:
Zuul encountered a syntax error while parsing its configuration in the
repo ansible/zuul-config on branch master.  The error was:

  The project template "ansible-collections-community-aws-integration"
  was not found.

The error appears in the following project stanza:

  project:
      name: ansible-collections/community.aws
      default-branch: main
      merge-mode: squash-merge
      templates:
        - system-required
        - publish-to-galaxy
        - ansible-collections-community-aws
        - ansible-collections-community-aws-integration

  in "ansible/zuul-config/zuul.d/projects.yaml@master", line 144, column 3

issue.title: Bump twisted from 22.8.0 to 22.10.0

labels.name: dependencies
labels.description: Pull requests that update a dependency file

issue.body:
Bumps [twisted](https://github.com/twisted/twisted) from 22.8.0 to 22.10.0.
Release notes

Sourced from twisted's releases.

Twisted 22.10.0 (2022-10-30)

This release contains a security fix for CVE-2022-39348. This is a low-severity security bug.

Twisted 22.10.0rc1 release candidate was released on 2022-10-26 and there are no changes between the release candidate and the final release.

Features

  • The systemd: endpoint parser now supports "named" file descriptors. This is a more reliable mechanism for choosing among several inherited descriptors. (#8147)

Improved Documentation

  • The systemd endpoint parser's index parameter is now documented as leading to non-deterministic results in which descriptor is selected. The new name parameter is now documented as preferred. (#8146)
  • The implementers of Zope interfaces are once more displayed in the documentations. (#11690)

Deprecations and Removals

  • twisted.protocols.dict, which was deprecated in 17.9, has been removed. (#11725)

Misc

  • #11573, #11599, #11616, #11628, #11631, #11640, #11645, #11647, #11652, #11664, #11674, #11679, #11686, #11692, #11694, #11696, #11700, #11702, #11713, #11715, #11721

Conch

Bugfixes


- twisted.conch.manhole.ManholeInterpreter now captures tracebacks even if sys.excepthook has been modified. ([#11638](https://github.com/twisted/twisted/issues/11638))

Web


Features

... (truncated)

Changelog

Sourced from twisted's changelog.

Twisted 22.10.0 (2022-10-30)

This release contains a security fix for CVE-2022-39348. This is a low-severity security bug.

Twisted 22.10.0rc1 release candidate was released on 2022-10-26 and there are no changes between the release candidate and the final release.

Features

  • The systemd: endpoint parser now supports "named" file descriptors. This is a more reliable mechanism for choosing among several inherited descriptors. (#8147)

Improved Documentation

  • The systemd endpoint parser's index parameter is now documented as leading to non-deterministic results in which descriptor is selected. The new name parameter is now documented as preferred. (#8146)
  • The implementers of Zope interfaces are once more displayed in the documentations. (#11690)

Deprecations and Removals

  • twisted.protocols.dict, which was deprecated in 17.9, has been removed. (#11725)

Misc

  • #11573, #11599, #11616, #11628, #11631, #11640, #11645, #11647, #11652, #11664, #11674, #11679, #11686, #11692, #11694, #11696, #11700, #11702, #11713, #11715, #11721

Conch

Bugfixes


- twisted.conch.manhole.ManholeInterpreter now captures tracebacks even if sys.excepthook has been modified. ([#11638](https://github.com/twisted/twisted/issues/11638))

Web


Features

issue.title: Welcome to support for indentation with spaces in to_xml plugin
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY
As requested in issue #116 , this PR introduces support for indentation using spaces instead of tabs.

Fixes #116 .

##### ISSUE TYPE
- Feature Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME
to_xml

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
The plugin now has two additional parameters:

* indent (string: can be "tabs" or "spaces", default to "tabs")
* indent_width (int: only used when indent="spaces", default to 4)

When `indent` is omitted or `indent='tabs'` , a single tab is forced as indentation (this is how the plugin always worked).

```yaml
- name: Define JSON data
  ansible.builtin.set_fact:
    data:
      "interface-configurations":
          "@xmlns": "http://cisco.com/ns/yang/Cisco-IOS-XR-ifmgr-cfg"
          "interface-configuration":
- debug:
    msg:  "{{ data|ansible.utils.to_xml(indent="spaces", indent_width=2) }}"
```

issue.title: Unable to open rpm-specs/coreutils-provides.inc: No such file or directory
issue.body:
I have very simple script:

```
#!/usr/bin/python3                                                                                             
from specfile import Specfile
import sys

# this is dumb, but do the work
filename = sys.argv[1]
specfile = Specfile(filename)

with specfile.sections() as sections:
    print(sections.changelog)

```
And when I run it as `./print-spec-changelog.py rpm-specs/coreutils.spec` I get:

```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/rpm.py", line 319, in parse
    spec = rpm.spec(tmp.name, rpm.RPMSPEC_ANYARCH | rpm.RPMSPEC_FORCE)
           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
ValueError: can't parse specfile


The above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/msuchy/projects/license-validate/./print-spec-changelog.py", line 7, in <module>
    specfile = Specfile(filename)
               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/specfile.py", line 48, in __init__
    self._spec = RPM.parse(str(self), self.sourcedir, self.macros)
                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/rpm.py", line 326, in parse
    raise RPMException(stderr=stderr) from e
specfile.exceptions.RPMException: Unable to open rpm-specs/coreutils-provides.inc: No such file or directory
```

The culprit is https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/coreutils/blob/rawhide/f/coreutils.spec#_13
Not sure who and why is trying to load the source file.

##### SUMMARY

- Refacter's the lookup plugins to use common code for common boto3/botocore operations
- Updates lookup module docs fragments to synchronise them with module parameters

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

Packit now allows to re-trigger Bodhi update via dist-git PR comment `/packit create-update`.
RELEASE NOTES END

issue.title: [WIP] Refacter lookup plugins

labels.name: feature
labels.description: This issue/PR relates to a feature request

issue.body:
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1227
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1231


##### SUMMARY

Splits up get_aws_region and get_aws_connection_info logic to reduce the requirement on module so that lookup modules can also use it too.

Refacters aws_account_attribute, aws_secret and aws_ssm lookup modules to use the common botocore connection code and parameters.

Moves AnsibleAWSException into module_utils.exceptions to avoid circular dependencies.

Updates lookup module docs fragments to synchronise them with module parameters
Updates lookup module docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Feature Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/lookup/aws_account_attribute.py
plugins/lookup/aws_secret.py
plugins/lookup/aws_ssm.py
plugins/module_utils/botocore.py
plugins/module_utils/core.py
plugins/module_utils/exceptions.py
plugins/module_utils/modules.py

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

issue.title: Refacter docs fragments and synchronize modules and plugins
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY

Move some of our docs fragments about to better reflect what they're for and the fact that we now have our own "amazon.aws..." namespace we can use.

- Synchronises the modules and plugins docs fragments (as far as possible)
- Updates plugin docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

Note: the `amazon.aws.common.plugins` fragment will necessitate some changes to the inventory and lookup plugins before use.  (See also #1225).  However, those changes will then bring them in line with the other modules

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Docs Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/docs_fragments

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

issue.title: Refacter docs fragments and synchronize modules and plugins
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY

Move some of our docs fragments about to better reflect what they're for and the fact that we now have our own "amazon.aws..." namespace we can use.

- Synchronises the modules and plugins docs fragments (as far as possible)
- Updates plugin docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

Note: the `amazon.aws.common.plugins` fragment will necessitate some changes to the inventory and lookup plugins before use.  (See also #1225).  However, those changes will then bring them in line with the other modules

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Docs Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/docs_fragments

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

Zuul encountered a syntax error while parsing its configuration in the
repo ansible/zuul-config on branch master.  The error was:

  The project template "ansible-collections-community-aws-integration"
  was not found.

The error appears in the following project stanza:

  project:
      name: ansible-collections/community.aws
      default-branch: main
      merge-mode: squash-merge
      templates:
        - system-required
        - publish-to-galaxy
        - ansible-collections-community-aws
        - ansible-collections-community-aws-integration

  in "ansible/zuul-config/zuul.d/projects.yaml@master", line 144, column 3

        queue: integrated-aws

issue.title: Bump twisted from 22.8.0 to 22.10.0

labels.name: dependencies
labels.description: Pull requests that update a dependency file

issue.body:
Bumps [twisted](https://github.com/twisted/twisted) from 22.8.0 to 22.10.0.
Release notes

Sourced from twisted's releases.

Twisted 22.10.0 (2022-10-30)

This release contains a security fix for CVE-2022-39348. This is a low-severity security bug.

Twisted 22.10.0rc1 release candidate was released on 2022-10-26 and there are no changes between the release candidate and the final release.

Features

  • The systemd: endpoint parser now supports "named" file descriptors. This is a more reliable mechanism for choosing among several inherited descriptors. (#8147)

Improved Documentation

  • The systemd endpoint parser's index parameter is now documented as leading to non-deterministic results in which descriptor is selected. The new name parameter is now documented as preferred. (#8146)
  • The implementers of Zope interfaces are once more displayed in the documentations. (#11690)

Deprecations and Removals

  • twisted.protocols.dict, which was deprecated in 17.9, has been removed. (#11725)

Misc

  • #11573, #11599, #11616, #11628, #11631, #11640, #11645, #11647, #11652, #11664, #11674, #11679, #11686, #11692, #11694, #11696, #11700, #11702, #11713, #11715, #11721

Conch

Bugfixes


- twisted.conch.manhole.ManholeInterpreter now captures tracebacks even if sys.excepthook has been modified. ([#11638](https://github.com/twisted/twisted/issues/11638))

Web


Features

... (truncated)

Changelog

Sourced from twisted's changelog.

Twisted 22.10.0 (2022-10-30)

This release contains a security fix for CVE-2022-39348. This is a low-severity security bug.

Twisted 22.10.0rc1 release candidate was released on 2022-10-26 and there are no changes between the release candidate and the final release.

Features

  • The systemd: endpoint parser now supports "named" file descriptors. This is a more reliable mechanism for choosing among several inherited descriptors. (#8147)

Improved Documentation

  • The systemd endpoint parser's index parameter is now documented as leading to non-deterministic results in which descriptor is selected. The new name parameter is now documented as preferred. (#8146)
  • The implementers of Zope interfaces are once more displayed in the documentations. (#11690)

Deprecations and Removals

  • twisted.protocols.dict, which was deprecated in 17.9, has been removed. (#11725)

Misc

  • #11573, #11599, #11616, #11628, #11631, #11640, #11645, #11647, #11652, #11664, #11674, #11679, #11686, #11692, #11694, #11696, #11700, #11702, #11713, #11715, #11721

Conch

Bugfixes


- twisted.conch.manhole.ManholeInterpreter now captures tracebacks even if sys.excepthook has been modified. ([#11638](https://github.com/twisted/twisted/issues/11638))

Web


Features

... (truncated)

Commits
  • 39ee213 Update news for final version.
  • 7e76513 python -m incremental.update Twisted --newversion 22.10.0
  • 3f1f502 Apply suggestions from twm.
  • 3185b01 Add info about CVE at the start of the release notes.
  • 15aa477 tox -e towncrier
  • 0a29d34 python -m incremental.update Twisted --rc
  • f2f5e81 Merge pull request from GHSA-vg46-2rrj-3647
  • b0545bc Merge branch 'trunk' into advisory-fix-1
  • 50761f4 #11715: Use NEXT in deprecation examples (#11720)
  • 927a5dc Add newsfragment
  • Additional commits viewable in compare view

issue.title: Welcome to support for indentation with spaces in to_xml plugin
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY
As requested in issue #116 , this PR introduces support for indentation using spaces instead of tabs.

Fixes #116 .

##### ISSUE TYPE
- Feature Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME
to_xml

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
The plugin now has two additional parameters:

* indent (string: can be "tabs" or "spaces", default to "tabs")
* indent_width (int: only used when indent="spaces", default to 4)

When `indent` is omitted or `indent='tabs'` , a single tab is forced as indentation (this is how the plugin always worked).

```yaml
- name: Define JSON data
  ansible.builtin.set_fact:
    data:
      "interface-configurations":
          "@xmlns": "http://cisco.com/ns/yang/Cisco-IOS-XR-ifmgr-cfg"
          "interface-configuration":
- debug:
    msg:  "{{ data|ansible.utils.to_xml(indent="spaces", indent_width=2) }}"
```

issue.title: Unable to open rpm-specs/coreutils-provides.inc: No such file or directory
issue.body:
I have very simple script:

```
#!/usr/bin/python3                                                                                             
from specfile import Specfile
import sys

# this is dumb, but do the work
filename = sys.argv[1]
specfile = Specfile(filename)

with specfile.sections() as sections:
    print(sections.changelog)

```
And when I run it as `./print-spec-changelog.py rpm-specs/coreutils.spec` I get:

```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/rpm.py", line 319, in parse
    spec = rpm.spec(tmp.name, rpm.RPMSPEC_ANYARCH | rpm.RPMSPEC_FORCE)
           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
ValueError: can't parse specfile


The above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/msuchy/projects/license-validate/./print-spec-changelog.py", line 7, in <module>
    specfile = Specfile(filename)
               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/specfile.py", line 48, in __init__
    self._spec = RPM.parse(str(self), self.sourcedir, self.macros)
                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/rpm.py", line 326, in parse
    raise RPMException(stderr=stderr) from e
specfile.exceptions.RPMException: Unable to open rpm-specs/coreutils-provides.inc: No such file or directory
```

The culprit is https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/coreutils/blob/rawhide/f/coreutils.spec#_13
Not sure who and why is trying to load the source file.

issue.title: [WIP] Refacter lookup plugins

labels.name: feature
labels.description: This issue/PR relates to a feature request

issue.body:
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1246
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1227
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1231


##### SUMMARY

- Refacter's the lookup plugins to use common code for common boto3/botocore operations
- Updates lookup module docs fragments to synchronise them with module parameters
- Updates lookup module docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations
- Adds 'boto3_profile' as an alias to 'profile' for consistency between modules and lookup plugins

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Feature Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/lookup/aws_account_attribute.py
plugins/lookup/aws_secret.py
plugins/lookup/aws_ssm.py
plugins/module_utils/botocore.py
plugins/module_utils/core.py
plugins/module_utils/exceptions.py
plugins/module_utils/modules.py

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

issue.title: Feat(bodhi): Retrigger bodhi update via dist-git PR command
issue.body:
I have rebased the Jirka K. work and I have used Mixins to manage Koji data needed to create a new bodhi update.

This comes from #1654

Fixes #1541

Merge after packit/packit#1764

- [x] call `is_packager` as aked by Laura: https://github.com/packit/packit-service/pull/1654#discussion_r994522524

Notes:
1. Since I am using [this method](https://github.com/packit/packit-service/blob/96a59e7b1ca4ecf2c68633ec64ff4f01a9f5cea0/packit_service/worker/checker/abstract.py#L39) if for any reason actor is `None` then the body update will succed, I don't know if this could be a problem.
2. Test are failing because the packit PR packit/packit#1764 is not yet merged.

---

RELEASE NOTES BEGIN
Packit now allows to re-trigger Bodhi update via dist-git PR comment `/packit create-update`.
RELEASE NOTES END

issue.title: [WIP] Refacter lookup plugins

labels.name: feature
labels.description: This issue/PR relates to a feature request

issue.body:
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1227
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1231


##### SUMMARY

Splits up get_aws_region and get_aws_connection_info logic to reduce the requirement on module so that lookup modules can also use it too.

Refacters aws_account_attribute, aws_secret and aws_ssm lookup modules to use the common botocore connection code and parameters.

Moves AnsibleAWSException into module_utils.exceptions to avoid circular dependencies.

Updates lookup module docs fragments to synchronise them with module parameters
Updates lookup module docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Feature Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/lookup/aws_account_attribute.py
plugins/lookup/aws_secret.py
plugins/lookup/aws_ssm.py
plugins/module_utils/botocore.py
plugins/module_utils/core.py
plugins/module_utils/exceptions.py
plugins/module_utils/modules.py

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

issue.title: Refacter docs fragments and synchronize modules and plugins
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY

Move some of our docs fragments about to better reflect what they're for and the fact that we now have our own "amazon.aws..." namespace we can use.

- Synchronises the modules and plugins docs fragments (as far as possible)
- Updates plugin docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

Note: the `amazon.aws.common.plugins` fragment will necessitate some changes to the inventory and lookup plugins before use.  (See also #1225).  However, those changes will then bring them in line with the other modules

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Docs Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/docs_fragments

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

issue.title: Refacter docs fragments and synchronize modules and plugins
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY

Move some of our docs fragments about to better reflect what they're for and the fact that we now have our own "amazon.aws..." namespace we can use.

- Synchronises the modules and plugins docs fragments (as far as possible)
- Updates plugin docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

Note: the `amazon.aws.common.plugins` fragment will necessitate some changes to the inventory and lookup plugins before use.  (See also #1225).  However, those changes will then bring them in line with the other modules

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Docs Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/docs_fragments

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

comment.body:
Zuul encountered a syntax error while parsing its configuration in the
repo ansible/zuul-config on branch master.  The error was:

  The project template "ansible-collections-community-aws-integration"
  was not found.

The error appears in the following project stanza:

  project:
      name: ansible-collections/community.aws
      default-branch: main
      merge-mode: squash-merge
      templates:
        - system-required
        - publish-to-galaxy
        - ansible-collections-community-aws
        - ansible-collections-community-aws-integration

  in "ansible/zuul-config/zuul.d/projects.yaml@master", line 144, column 3

issue.title: Bump twisted from 22.8.0 to 22.10.0

labels.name: dependencies
labels.description: Pull requests that update a dependency file

issue.body:
Bumps [twisted](https://github.com/twisted/twisted) from 22.8.0 to 22.10.0.
Release notes

Sourced from twisted's releases.

Twisted 22.10.0 (2022-10-30)

This release contains a security fix for CVE-2022-39348. This is a low-severity security bug.

Twisted 22.10.0rc1 release candidate was released on 2022-10-26 and there are no changes between the release candidate and the final release.

Features

  • The systemd: endpoint parser now supports "named" file descriptors. This is a more reliable mechanism for choosing among several inherited descriptors. (#8147)

Improved Documentation

  • The systemd endpoint parser's index parameter is now documented as leading to non-deterministic results in which descriptor is selected. The new name parameter is now documented as preferred. (#8146)
  • The implementers of Zope interfaces are once more displayed in the documentations. (#11690)

Deprecations and Removals

  • twisted.protocols.dict, which was deprecated in 17.9, has been removed. (#11725)

Misc

  • #11573, #11599, #11616, #11628, #11631, #11640, #11645, #11647, #11652, #11664, #11674, #11679, #11686, #11692, #11694, #11696, #11700, #11702, #11713, #11715, #11721

Conch

Bugfixes


- twisted.conch.manhole.ManholeInterpreter now captures tracebacks even if sys.excepthook has been modified. ([#11638](https://github.com/twisted/twisted/issues/11638))

Web

... (truncated)

issue.title: Welcome to support for indentation with spaces in to_xml plugin
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY
As requested in issue #116 , this PR introduces support for indentation using spaces instead of tabs.

Fixes #116 .

##### ISSUE TYPE
- Feature Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME
to_xml

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
The plugin now has two additional parameters:

* indent (string: can be "tabs" or "spaces", default to "tabs")
* indent_width (int: only used when indent="spaces", default to 4)

When `indent` is omitted or `indent='tabs'` , a single tab is forced as indentation (this is how the plugin always worked).

```yaml
- name: Define JSON data
  ansible.builtin.set_fact:
    data:
      "interface-configurations":
          "@xmlns": "http://cisco.com/ns/yang/Cisco-IOS-XR-ifmgr-cfg"
          "interface-configuration":
- debug:
    msg:  "{{ data|ansible.utils.to_xml(indent="spaces", indent_width=2) }}"
```

issue.title: Unable to open rpm-specs/coreutils-provides.inc: No such file or directory
issue.body:
I have very simple script:

```
#!/usr/bin/python3                                                                                             
from specfile import Specfile
import sys

# this is dumb, but do the work
filename = sys.argv[1]
specfile = Specfile(filename)

with specfile.sections() as sections:
    print(sections.changelog)

```
And when I run it as `./print-spec-changelog.py rpm-specs/coreutils.spec` I get:

```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/rpm.py", line 319, in parse
    spec = rpm.spec(tmp.name, rpm.RPMSPEC_ANYARCH | rpm.RPMSPEC_FORCE)
           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
ValueError: can't parse specfile


The above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/msuchy/projects/license-validate/./print-spec-changelog.py", line 7, in <module>
    specfile = Specfile(filename)
               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/specfile.py", line 48, in __init__
    self._spec = RPM.parse(str(self), self.sourcedir, self.macros)
                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  File "/usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/specfile/rpm.py", line 326, in parse
    raise RPMException(stderr=stderr) from e
specfile.exceptions.RPMException: Unable to open rpm-specs/coreutils-provides.inc: No such file or directory
```

The culprit is https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/coreutils/blob/rawhide/f/coreutils.spec#_13
Not sure who and why is trying to load the source file.

issue.body:
I have rebased the Jirka K. work and I have used Mixins to manage Koji data needed to create a new bodhi update.

This comes from #1654

Fixes #1541

Merge after packit/packit#1764

- [x] call `is_packager` as aked by Laura: https://github.com/packit/packit-service/pull/1654#discussion_r994522524

Notes:
1. Since I am using [this method](https://github.com/packit/packit-service/blob/96a59e7b1ca4ecf2c68633ec64ff4f01a9f5cea0/packit_service/worker/checker/abstract.py#L39) if for any reason actor is `None` then the body update will succed, I don't know if this could be a problem.
2. Test are failing because the packit PR packit/packit#1764 is not yet merged.

---

RELEASE NOTES BEGIN
Packit now allows to re-trigger Bodhi update via dist-git PR comment `/packit create-update`.
RELEASE NOTES END

issue.title: [WIP] Refacter lookup plugins

labels.name: feature

issue.body:
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1227
Depends-On: https://github.com/ansible-collections/amazon.aws/pull/1231


##### SUMMARY

Splits up get_aws_region and get_aws_connection_info logic to reduce the requirement on module so that lookup modules can also use it too.

Refacters aws_account_attribute, aws_secret and aws_ssm lookup modules to use the common botocore connection code and parameters.

Moves AnsibleAWSException into module_utils.exceptions to avoid circular dependencies.

Updates lookup module docs fragments to synchronise them with module parameters
Updates lookup module docs fragments to reflect the previously announced env variable deprecations

plugins/lookup/aws_account_attribute.py

plugins/lookup/aws_ssm.py

issue.title: vmware_guest_custom_attributes: Improve the code quality and add the return value for the diff
issue.body:
##### SUMMARY

The same function executes when the state is present and absent in vmware_guest_custom_attributes module.  
I didn't think it was good code, so I refactored the function to split it for each purpose.  
And added the return value for diff as we can be checked the custom attribute difference.

related: https://github.com/ansible-collections/community.vmware/issues/1484

##### ISSUE TYPE

- Feature Pull Request

##### COMPONENT NAME

plugins/modules/vmware_guest_custom_attributes.py
tests/integration/targets/vmware_guest_custom_attributes/tasks/main.yml
changelogs/fragments/1532-vmware_guest_custom_attributes.yml

##### ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

tested on VCSA 7.0.0
